1
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:07,000
(Previously)
Can you split that with me?

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:07,480
(Ding's down)
Sure.

3
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:09,840
- ♪Half each♪
- ♪Half each♪

4
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,240
(Solo mission incoming)
Honestly, nothing happened to me.

5
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,000
In my hallway, I mean.

6
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,280
Then why were you screaming like that?

7
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,000
(Even He was shook)
I was scared.

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,800
(Asking for hard mode)
Zhang Linghe wants hard mode.

9
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:16,760
Even with no one there,

10
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:18,640
I was screaming my head off.

11
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:19,600
Were you scared, Ning?

12
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,360
(Barely holding on)
I was terrified.

13
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,520
I yelled "Jin Jing" in there.

14
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:22,160
Did you hear me?

15
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:22,560
Nope.

16
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:24,000
(Scared? Call Jin first)
I yelled, "Jin Jing"!

17
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:24,720
And she was like, "Okay".

18
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,120
(Evil Jin takes over)
I'll come out and scare you myself.

19
00:00:26,620 --> 00:00:27,600
(Ready to drop in)

20
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,200
Zhou, you look awesome.

21
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,080
Zhou Keyu looks like he does this
for a living.

22
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:32,360
(Perfect fit)

23
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:33,560
Why do you look so legit?

24
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:35,020
Honestly, this feels like my real job.

25
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:36,000
(Straight out of an action movie)
Okay, let's do it.

26
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:36,720
Okay.

27
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:38,640
Three, two, one, go.

28
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:46,940
(Gun-and-staff duo)

29
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,140
(Cool-girl duo)

30
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,260
(Bow-and-crossbow team)

31
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:51,200
Everyone, give me a shocked look.

32
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,240
So we're doing shocked?

33
00:00:52,580 --> 00:00:53,380
(Ke's shocked face)

34
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:56,940
(Ding copies Ke's shock)

35
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:58,740
(Ning's shocked face)

36
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,040
(Curious)
I want to see Zhang Linghe do shocked.

37
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:03,100
(He's shocked face)

38
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:10,140
=Truth Clubhouse=

39
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:13,140
(The cafe is open, calm as ever)

40
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,640
Ke, let's get you on your mark first.

41
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,200
(Suspicious)
Wait, are you the actual killer?

42
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:19,120
(The lead detective)
I'm the detective. How am I the killer?

43
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,680
(Wrong person to mess with)
He's the detective, okay?

44
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,880
Say that again,

45
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:23,320
(Remember who's in charge today)
and I'll arrest you, Ding.

46
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:26,000
(Ke has entered boss mode)
Questioning my authority now?

47
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,320
Chief.

48
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,280
You're the chief today.

49
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,200
I'm the chief today.

50
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:31,780
(Make way)

51
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:33,320
(Smile it off)

52
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:34,160
Let's go.

53
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,560
Good luck, detective.

54
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,800
You're all done for. I'm telling you.

55
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:37,800
Just wait.

56
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:38,960
(Qian enters boss mode)
Game on.

57
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,080
Come on. She just threatened you.

58
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:40,680
What do you want to say?

59
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,160
I think

60
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,000
we need to give Sun Qian some credit.

61
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,640
After recording
the first episode yesterday,

62
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,320
she kept thinking
about what she could do better.

63
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:47,840
(Best support player)
She went through it with me past 2AM.

64
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,840
She said,
"Tomorrow, I'm going to be brave".

65
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:51,900
(Qian is putting in work)

66
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:53,400
Want to check your script again?

67
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,800
(Eyes wide open)
What script?

68
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,600
Your killer script.

69
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:00,340
(Ding can say no wrong)

70
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,240
Killer? What killer?

71
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:01,960
(Keyword detected)
Who's the killer?

72
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:03,240
You're already talking killers?

73
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,040
Why wasn't I part of this?

74
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,880
I'm the killer.

75
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,680
We were talking about Popeye.

76
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,680
Killer.

77
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,920
(Casually throws everyone under the bus)
Jin is the killer today.

78
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:12,760
Wait.

79
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,960
You're acting weird.

80
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:14,400
You said,

81
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,080
"I'm the killer"?

82
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:16,760
I'm the killer.

83
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,600
(Not playing along)

84
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,280
You're confessing already?

85
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,080
Vote for me.

86
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,080
Not even pretending anymore?

87
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:21,400
Vote me.

88
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,960
(He buys it)
Whatever you do, I'm on your side.

89
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,600
(Hooked)
My vote is always yours.

90
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:27,940
(It's all fake)

91
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,280
So that's just painted black?

92
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:29,900
(Learned something)

93
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,680
I said it's just painted black.

94
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,080
Everyone came so dressed up.

95
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,840
You're dressed up too.

96
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,160
All glitter and glam.

97
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,240
We're all here

98
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,760
(Smooth talker)
to serve you, of course.

99
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,720
Sun Qian today...

100
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:41,440
She went in there.

101
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,640
She was in there with Ke.

102
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,240
She's the detective today.

103
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,360
She stayed up last night,

104
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,760
doing serious homework.

105
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,200
Seriously?

106
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,160
(Overachiever)
Seriously?

107
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:48,960
Who?

108
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,080
Sun Qian.

109
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,240
She felt like yesterday's performance

110
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,320
could've been better.

111
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,280
So she really studied up.

112
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,240
(Good job, Qian)
Still reviewing after 2AM.

113
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,440
I was asleep way before that.

114
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,700
(Jin's healthy era missed all the drama)

115
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,640
You've changed.

116
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,800
I was reviewing in silence too.

117
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:03,220
(Look at you)

118
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,300
(Sheepish)

119
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,400
You've changed.

120
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:07,120
(Takes that exit back)
Rolling?

121
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:07,480
Jin.

122
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:10,880
Come on.

123
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,440
Three, two, one.

124
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:13,220
(Perfectly locked in)

125
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,200
(Meanwhile)

126
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,520
(In character already)
How are we supposed to win this?

127
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,640
I don't think we can.

128
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:18,640
Like this?

129
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,280
I guess we just...

130
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:20,840
Work on our grip strength.

131
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,240
Right.

132
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,760
(Making small talk)
How'd you sleep last night?

133
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,160
Great.

134
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:26,920
I slept so well.

135
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:28,360
What time did you go to bed?

136
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,680
2AM.

137
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,560
Same, pretty much.

138
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:32,420
(Good night, Makka Pakka)

139
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,040
Got tired after a while.

140
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,080
Today's all physical challenges.

141
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:38,680
Really?

142
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,440
Yep, all of it.

143
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,640
What are we doing?

144
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,040
Hauling cement.

145
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:43,660
(Totally making it up)

146
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,000
I don't know.

147
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,080
Last time, we...

148
00:03:48,820 --> 00:03:50,060
(Totally confused)

149
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,400
Have you ever been electrocuted?

150
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,280
No.

151
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,640
We had to do pull-ups

152
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,720
while holding this thing,

153
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,720
and it was electrified.

154
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,340
(The Truth Season 4 teaser)

155
00:03:58,720 --> 00:03:59,720
Everyone had to?

156
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,880
Yeah. It shocks you.

157
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,120
Your whole upper body.

158
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:03,880
Like, actually shocks you?

159
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:04,480
Really.

160
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:05,500
(Terrified)

161
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,120
Really.

162
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,280
So you're doing pull-ups
while getting shocked.

163
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:08,760
It's awesome.

164
00:04:09,420 --> 00:04:10,140
(Wait, what?)

165
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,800
It hurts at first, then...

166
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,600
(Too honest)
Then you go numb.

167
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,000
Yeah, numb.

168
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,390
Was the last episode fun?

169
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:17,950
Last episode?

170
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:19,480
That one was pretty hard.

171
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,720
Harder than this one.

172
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,120
Really?

173
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,920
(Hard to forget)
Last episode had six killers.

174
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:23,920
Six killers?

175
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:24,640
How many people total?

176
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,520
Four killers.

177
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,460
(Memory failed)

178
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:28,500
(The suspects are chilling)

179
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,160
Is anyone filming this?

180
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:32,740
(Getting cheeky)

181
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:34,400
(Show us the muscles)
Let me see.

182
00:04:35,020 --> 00:04:36,340
(My turn)

183
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,360
You...

184
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,560
(I work out too)
I've got one too.

185
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:39,720
(Nodding like crazy)
She does.

186
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,720
She does.

187
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,440
She has one too.

188
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,080
From carrying the baby around.

189
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,200
The doctor
said not to carry him too much.

190
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,760
Like, for a year...

191
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,960
For a year and a half, don't carry him.

192
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,920
(Dead serious)
He'll get spoiled, right?

193
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,720
Why do you believe

194
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,960
everything people tell you?

195
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,320
Our whole generation

196
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,480
(Gen Z speaking from experience)
got carried around.

197
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,720
Your generation did too.

198
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,720
I got carried too.

199
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,680
Now suddenly we can't?

200
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:58,500
(Confused)

201
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,400
Why?

202
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,000
My parents carried me all the time
when I was growing up.

203
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:01,280
So what?

204
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,360
All three of us

205
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,360
got carried growing up.

206
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,320
Did we turn out that bad?

207
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,720
Parent with science,

208
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,920
(Words of wisdom)
not superstition.

209
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:09,720
He said

210
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,200
carrying the baby too much
hurts his back.

211
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:12,880
He's looking out for you, then.

212
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,680
(Looking out for Mom)
Yeah.

213
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,840
(That's true)
Recording starts.

214
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,800
Three, two, one.

215
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,760
Let's go. We...

216
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,920
It's them.

217
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:21,890
(Romance watchdog activated)
Those two are gaming together.

218
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:23,700
(What now?)

219
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,680
He's playing a game

220
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,280
with his girlfriend's best friend.

221
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:27,360
(That feels wrong)
Interesting, right?

222
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,760
Is that allowed?

223
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,860
(A little too far)

224
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:31,620
(Romance watchdog says no)

225
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,680
You're just

226
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,520
not interested anymore, are you?

227
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,080
What do you mean?

228
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,200
Your idol, remember?

229
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,280
(Sudden concern)
How did you sleep last night?

230
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,160
I'm just a fan, honestly.

231
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:40,760
Just a fan

232
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,240
(100% pure fan)
in the story.

233
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,600
A career fan?

234
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,640
Yeah, a career fan.

235
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,960
But I think

236
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:46,840
any fan

237
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,120
who saw their idol

238
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,080
get hurt like that yesterday

239
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:49,640
would be worried.

240
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,000
Come on, let's check on him.

241
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,040
You have zero concern.

242
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:52,640
All I see

243
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,960
is someone happy to clock out soon.

244
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,460
(Reasonable suspicion)

245
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:55,560
Let's go.

246
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,380
(Back to work)

247
00:05:57,460 --> 00:06:00,380
(Solo mission unlocked, cue the panic)

248
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,440
It's safe here.

249
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,280
(Don't be scared)
Really?

250
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:03,040
Yeah, you're good.

251
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:04,320
Who is that?

252
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:04,800
Me.

253
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,200
Don't panic.

254
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:06,940
(Which one of us is nervous?)

255
00:06:06,940 --> 00:06:08,780
(Ahhh!)

256
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,500
(VIP front-row seat)

257
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,960
You're going too?

258
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:15,280
Yeah.

259
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,400
(#Scared and full of questions)
Why are you going too?

260
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,040
(Question +1)
Do you go through here every day?

261
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,680
(Question +2)
Do you scream when you go through?

262
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,920
(Question +3)
Is this your first time too?

263
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,120
I have night blindness.

264
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,240
(Question +4)
Is it really this dark,

265
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,000
huh?

266
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:26,520
(Am I asking too much?)

267
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,880
Actually, I can't see either.

268
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,240
I'm completely blind here.

269
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:29,680
Right.

270
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,560
If you look up at the ceiling,

271
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,920
you can see the infrared lights, right?

272
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,360
Yep.

273
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,200
I looked up videos of you guys online.

274
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,320
I saw you all

275
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,680
just walk around. How?

276
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,160
By feeling around.

277
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,120
Just touch and go?

278
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:40,920
(Pro tip)
Yep. Pure touch.

279
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,560
So he's not scared at all.

280
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,400
I mean, Bai Yu.

281
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:44,800
Right.

282
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,720
I saw it.

283
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,080
He can even catch "ghosts".

284
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,040
At first, he leads us through.

285
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,360
But after a while,

286
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,680
once the lights go off,
he ditches the group.

287
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,160
Then he goes off and has fun by himself.

288
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,880
So did this make you braver?

289
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,040
For sure.

290
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:58,200
(The screaming stopped)

291
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,360
It doesn't feel that scary now.

292
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,080
No one's even screaming now.

293
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,080
They're chatting.

294
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,920
Maybe at first
someone touched something.

295
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:04,400
I can probably

296
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,280
in the dark...

297
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,160
(Sudden genre shift)
touch up my lipstick.

298
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,020
(Searching by feel)

299
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,000
I can't find my lips.

300
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,100
(Can't see a thing)

301
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,200
I can't find my lips,

302
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,200
and now I can't even get it back
into the tube.

303
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,320
You're making me nervous.

304
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,360
You sure you can handle this job?

305
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,520
I really can't find it.

306
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:23,900
(Try again)

307
00:07:24,780 --> 00:07:25,860
(Cracking herself up)

308
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,280
I still can't get it back into the tube.

309
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:29,440
Come here.

310
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:30,640
(Night vision mode)
Where?

311
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,160
Here.

312
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:31,800
(Mirror reflection)
Can you see?

313
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,480
See if the reflection helps.

314
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:35,240
He's blocking the light.

315
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,120
(Negotiating)
Let me cap my lipstick first.

316
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,480
He's trying to film you.

317
00:07:39,740 --> 00:07:41,540
(Red light on)

318
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:42,480
The red light's on.

319
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,360
Then let's stand

320
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,240
by our doors.

321
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:44,680
Let's go.

322
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,440
Which door am I again?

323
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,520
You're Door Two.

324
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:48,480
I can't see.

325
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,640
Is this Door Two?

326
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:50,380
(Lights suddenly on)
Oh, my god.

327
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:51,880
It's fine.

328
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,480
Let's just get in position first.

329
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:54,880
What was that?

330
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,040
Motion light.

331
00:07:56,660 --> 00:07:56,780
(Hey!)

332
00:07:58,620 --> 00:07:59,460
(Ready to go)

333
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,280
Open your door.

334
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,560
(Made it)
Come over here!

335
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,100
(Still shaken)

336
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,560
You couldn't handle it?

337
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,120
(Braver now)
He grabbed my leg.

338
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,600
I pulled him along with me.

339
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,440
Someone grabbed your leg?

340
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:10,800
Yeah.

341
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:11,600
Yep.

342
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,260
(Me too)

343
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,320
Were you scared, Li Fei?

344
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:15,800
(Acting tough)
It's my house. Why would I be scared?

345
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,510
(Plotting)
Let's scare them.

346
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,960
Let's hide and jump-scare those two.

347
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:21,800
What happened?

348
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:22,960
Meaning?

349
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:23,840
We wait for them.

350
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,080
They'll come out
through these two doors.

351
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,480
(He can't hide his mischief)
We hide in the corner.

352
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,720
You guys are terrible.

353
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,040
(Slides right into the plan)
We just stay quiet.

354
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,880
Act like we're not here.

355
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:31,740
(Sneaking around)

356
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:32,820
(I'm in too)

357
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,700
(Ahhh!)

358
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:36,500
(Holding on tight)

359
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:37,780
(Just thinking about it)

360
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:40,020
(Never too tired for mischief)

361
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,120
You...

362
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,240
He, you're trying to scare people now?

363
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,400
You were screaming just now.

364
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,140
(Still rattled)

365
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,520
You did it. You leveled up.

366
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,440
Thank God I could hear your voices.

367
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,080
If I couldn't, I would've panicked.

368
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,520
Was someone holding you up?

369
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:56,440
Or pulling you along?

370
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,600
He grabbed my leg.

371
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,960
Then I grabbed his hand.

372
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,840
So I just followed him the whole way.

373
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,240
Then he shined a flashlight on his face,

374
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,160
so I peeked too.

375
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,280
I tried to take his flashlight,

376
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:05,960
(Poor thing)
but he wouldn't let me.

377
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,280
(Same here)
I tried to take his flashlight too.

378
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,800
It's okay. You leveled up.

379
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,600
(Xin comforts her)
It's okay. You almost here.

380
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,080
They definitely

381
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,320
made it extra scary for her.

382
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:16,600
Yeah.

383
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:18,240
(Night vision mode)
No way.

384
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,120
They wouldn't do that to her.

385
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,680
(Not convinced)
I think they're trying to scare her.

386
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,000
Qian's behind you, right?

387
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,640
Yeah.

388
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,680
Is there anyone on your side?

389
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:25,480
No one on my side.

390
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:26,920
No one?

391
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,680
I have someone.

392
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,000
(Reporting the trauma)
Someone grabbed my leg

393
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,040
and flashed a white light.

394
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,480
Wait, someone's behind me.
Who's walking?

395
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,480
(Leader Li is strolling)
Me.

396
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,480
Leader Li,
why are you walking behind me?

397
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,520
Honestly, I'm pretty scared too.

398
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,080
(Are you new here too?)
You've never done this before?

399
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,880
(Can't reveal too much)
I don't know anything either.

400
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,680
You got this!

401
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:47,820
(Voice from above: you got this)

402
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,840
Even the big guy upstairs showed up.

403
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,040
Why didn't the big guy upstairs

404
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,160
(I want encouragement too)
cheer me on earlier?

405
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,480
Because he thinks you're doing great.

406
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,720
(Aren't you brave?)
You were trying to grab the flashlight.

407
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:56,840
Ning!

408
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:58,240
Where?

409
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,040
Go straight. You'll feel the door.

410
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,160
Turn left.

411
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:01,680
Go to the end.

412
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,880
Use your hands

413
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,600
(Careful guidance)
along the walls and stuff.

414
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,000
Right.

415
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:05,920
Qian.

416
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,240
Qian Jingding.

417
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,120
Can you hear me?

418
00:10:08,660 --> 00:10:09,980
(Busy surviving)

419
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,240
It's here.

420
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:12,520
This door.

421
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,160
Pull...

422
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:13,520
it.

423
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,440
Once you're here, it opens.

424
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,920
(Finally out)
Come on.

425
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,760
Quick.

426
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,920
Hug me.

427
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,000
(Warm encouragement)
You made it.

428
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,440
Weren't you supposed
to get braver today?

429
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,640
I didn't expect to start
with a solo mission.

430
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:26,340
(Wasn't ready)

431
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:27,840
(Hair)

432
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,920
Did you guys have this thing drop down,

433
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:29,160
right?

434
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,520
Who had this drop down?

435
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,000
Who was Door Two?

436
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,600
(It's me)
Me.

437
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,200
Hair dropped down,

438
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,560
and there was this picture too.

439
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,760
See? Someone was trying to scare us.

440
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,760
(Caught you)

441
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:40,360
I saw it.

442
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:42,800
What?

443
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:43,560
(Curious)

444
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,200
I'm not telling you.

445
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,220
(Keeping it mysterious)

446
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,060
(Tiny rage)
No one's protecting you later.

447
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:48,540
(Still not telling)

448
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,480
There was someone standing there.

449
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:50,840
Right.

450
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,000
You okay? Nobody was there, right?

451
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,240
There was.
Someone was standing right there.

452
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,440
(Qian was begging)
I literally knelt there

453
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,920
and said, "Please don't touch me".

454
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,040
The cameraman, right?

455
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,240
The cameraman?

456
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,200
(Scared over nothing)

457
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,200
We all had people

458
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,160
with really realistic makeup,

459
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,920
shining flashlights on their own faces,

460
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:03,920
then coming over to grab your leg.

461
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:05,820
(Vivid reenactment)

462
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:06,760
Really?

463
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,480
You got the easy route.

464
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,240
Did they grab your leg?

465
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:10,680
They did.

466
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,160
The big guy upstairs
already encouraged me.

467
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,560
He said, "Sun Qian, you got this".

468
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,920
Sun Qian, you got this.

469
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,520
Don't be scared. You got this.

470
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:17,360
You know,

471
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,560
if the voice hadn't encouraged you,

472
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,560
we were all ready to scare you guys.

473
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,280
Not us.

474
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,120
(Someone)
Someone was.

475
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:24,880
Seriously? Trying to scare us?

476
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:25,960
She said it.

477
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:26,520
She said,

478
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,840
"Let's scare Sun Qian later".

479
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:29,660
(Ning, really?)

480
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,480
She really said it.

481
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,080
(Proof)
Check the footage if you don't trust me.

482
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:34,620
(Thought you could get away with it?)

483
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,160
(Still snitching)
Ding said it too.

484
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,080
Yeah, let's scare them.

485
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:40,940
(The prank trio)

486
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,120
Is that what happened?

487
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,140
(Got it)

488
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:45,100
(Let me see)

489
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,200
So in your hallway,

490
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,120
there were people like that?

491
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,360
I never opened my eyes.

492
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,220
(Eyes stayed shut)

493
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,960
(Genuinely curious)
How did you walk with your eyes closed?

494
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,680
(Couldn't open them, so I felt my way)
Did you touch him?

495
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:54,720
No.

496
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:56,700
(Pretty impressive)

497
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,480
(Full confession)
Honestly, nothing happened to me.

498
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,160
In my hallway, I mean.

499
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,040
I stepped on some poppers.

500
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,040
That was it, just poppers.

501
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,560
You didn't even get a person?

502
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,560
(Lucky duck)
Nothing.

503
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,920
Then why were you screaming like that?

504
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,480
(Just scared)
I was scared.

505
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,400
(Requesting hard mode)
Zhang Linghe wants hard mode.

506
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,600
He says nothing happened.

507
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:17,040
He said it didn't scare him at all.

508
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,360
(Secret assist)
Right.

509
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,720
(Turning it up)
He said it was too easy.

510
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,320
Even with no one there,

511
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:23,000
(If someone were there, I'd be finished)
I was screaming my head off.

512
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:24,960
Did yours have...

513
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,720
that sticky stuff?

514
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:27,920
No.

515
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,840
(Not buying it)
Were you scared? Be honest.

516
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,480
No, seriously,

517
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,400
he wasn't scared at all.

518
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,720
(Who says I wasn't?)
I was so scared my soul left my body.

519
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:35,280
You know?

520
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,280
(So dramatic)
Your soul left your body? Really?

521
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,440
(Ke says)
There's no way he's scared.

522
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:41,720
(Ning says)
There's no way he's scared.

523
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,160
Right.

524
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,280
(Cut it out)
Don't try...

525
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,560
Don't try that fake confidence boost
on me.

526
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,760
He really doesn't scare easily.

527
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:47,400
I think you guys

528
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,320
actually got into Zhang Linghe's head.

529
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,000
For real, I suddenly feel like...

530
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,440
(I really was scared)
I almost fell to my knees in there.

531
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,400
Impossible.

532
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:55,920
He's not scared.

533
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,160
Were you scared, Ning?

534
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,880
I was terrified.

535
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:00,960
Ning is definitely braver than I am.

536
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:01,920
He kept calming me down.

537
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,520
I was screaming in there.

538
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,760
I yelled "Jin Jing" in there.

539
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,320
Did you hear me?

540
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,360
Nope.

541
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,160
(Scared? Call Jin first)
I yelled, "Jin Jing"!

542
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,560
And she was like, "Okay."

543
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,080
(Evil Jin takes over)
I'll come out and scare you myself.

544
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:17,260
(I was scared, okay?)

545
00:13:17,420 --> 00:13:18,900
(Transition)
This factory is seriously scary.

546
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:21,140
Honestly, this place
is scarier than the actual set.

547
00:13:21,140 --> 00:13:23,140
No one has to walk
through here later, right?

548
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,740
Would you dare go through here alone?

549
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,220
This is even scarier
with the lights off.

550
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,900
Because it feels too real.

551
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:31,140
Who picked up all the poppers?

552
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:32,500
Jin, Jin...

553
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,460
Were you picking up poppers
and throwing them the whole time?

554
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:35,340
Yeah.

555
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:36,860
Jin, Jin...

556
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:37,980
Blah, blah, blah.

557
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:40,980
(Please collect your prop)

558
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,500
(Qian Jingding has arrived)

559
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:44,020
(Filming props)
Oh, god.

560
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:45,220
(He Yiwei has arrived)

561
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:47,780
(Ding Pudding has arrived)

562
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,580
(Film props. Do not imitate)

563
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:52,380
(Prop handout)

564
00:13:53,660 --> 00:13:55,060
(Your prop is here)

565
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,140
(Jin Cardashian has arrived)

566
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:59,100
(Target spotted)

567
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,060
(#Chaos siblings attack)

568
00:14:00,060 --> 00:14:01,580
(Hands up)

569
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:03,500
(Do you surrender?)

570
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:04,760
(Collecting props)
Here's your prop.

571
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:06,480
(Only you get one?)
You're under arrest.

572
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,520
Wait, Jin.

573
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,440
There's no key for that.

574
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,200
So don't play with it.

575
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,400
(Out of moves, huh?)
Almost.

576
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:13,640
Zhang Linghe almost had to film in that.

577
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,060
(I'm warning you)

578
00:14:16,140 --> 00:14:17,380
(Truce)

579
00:14:17,420 --> 00:14:18,980
(Ke Coffee has arrived)

580
00:14:19,020 --> 00:14:20,100
(Collecting gear)

581
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,100
(Obsessed)

582
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,440
(Ning Bubble has arrived)
Ning, can we check

583
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,560
this sample together?

584
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:27,440
Walk forward like you mean business.

585
00:14:27,620 --> 00:14:29,980
(Staring)

586
00:14:30,780 --> 00:14:32,300
(Can't look away)

587
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,240
Vertical foregrip.

588
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:36,340
(Jealous)

589
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:40,380
(Checking the gear)

590
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:43,340
(Practicing first)

591
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,440
That didn't have enough snap.

592
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,360
Anyone here know how to crack a whip?

593
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,040
(Asking the experts)

594
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,000
Have you learned it before?

595
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,400
As an actor,

596
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,760
you end up learning all kinds
of random stuff.

597
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:53,340
(Let me try)

598
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:55,460
(Trying again)

599
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:56,640
Fake whip.

600
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,240
Qian.

601
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:00,440
I'm right here.

602
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:01,600
Come here.

603
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,080
(Food coma)
I'm so sleepy after eating.

604
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,120
So sleepy.

605
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,080
Me too. So sleepy.

606
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,120
Come on.

607
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,240
Here.

608
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:10,000
(Action mode)
This is the villain, the killer.

609
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,240
Make it feel intimidating, everyone.

610
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,720
Add your own moves if you want.

611
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,080
Everyone.

612
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,460
(Working on the pose)

613
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,720
Try cracking it.

614
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,360
See if...

615
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,680
(Jin's genius tip)
Use your left hand.

616
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,400
Wait. Don't hit us in the face.

617
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,640
(Already beat up)
Zhang Linghe looks hit already.

618
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:23,520
That's scary.

619
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,360
The most valuable thing

620
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,200
I have is my face.

621
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,980
(Messing around)
I'll hit right here.

622
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,640
Any hit is a bonus.

623
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,220
(You better be careful)

624
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,020
(Who should be careful?)

625
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:35,860
(I'm sorry)

626
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:36,840
Okay, let's do it.

627
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:37,560
Okay.

628
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,480
Three, two, one, go!

629
00:15:47,420 --> 00:15:48,780
(Gun-and-staff bros)

630
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:50,540
(Cool-girl duo)

631
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:52,320
(Bow-and-crossbow partners)

632
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,240
That was great.

633
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:53,720
Let's

634
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,320
do it again.

635
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:06,140
(Wasteland squad, assemble)

636
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:14,460
(Film props. Do not imitate)

637
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:15,700
(Lone wolf Ding, full-aura Ning)

638
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:17,500
(Dashing Qian, bold and lively Jin)

639
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,340
(Cool and sharp He,
fierce and focused Ke)

640
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,160
Now everyone, look surprised.

641
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,440
We're going for surprise?

642
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:25,820
(Ke-style shock)

643
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,340
(Ding's take on Ke-style shock)

644
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:33,540
(Ning-style shock)

645
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,000
(Curious)
Let's see how He looks surprised.

646
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:39,100
(He's shocked)

647
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:39,660
(Surprised enough?)

648
00:16:40,140 --> 00:16:41,020
(Yep)

649
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,400
But don't overdo it.

650
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,120
Yeah, that works.

651
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:44,740
(Effortless control)

652
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,460
(Calm and focused)

653
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,620
(Perfectly balanced)

654
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,060
(Seriously shocked)

655
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:52,920
Okay, remove the table.

656
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,640
Then I won't have anything to lean on.

657
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:55,640
Let me hold onto you.

658
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:01,800
Okay, good.

659
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,440
Yep, my peripheral vision
on this side...

660
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:09,819
(To solve the case,
go wild and charge ahead)

661
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,069
Come on, Ke.

662
00:17:11,069 --> 00:17:12,000
(Big bro Ding, little bro Ke)

663
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:12,880
Give your bro a pull.

664
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,589
You've done a lot of wire work, right?

665
00:17:15,349 --> 00:17:15,880
A fair amount.

666
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,109
I'm only on wires a few times a year.

667
00:17:18,109 --> 00:17:20,069
(Flight mode, always on)
We're only off wires a few days a year.

668
00:17:20,859 --> 00:17:22,180
(Ke cracks up)

669
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:23,760
He has to fly too.

670
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:24,640
And fight.

671
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,160
Right.

672
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,800
(Hardcore "He" skills)
That's not all. I have to run across

673
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,200
rooftops and walls.

674
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:28,280
And he also...

675
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,840
(I swear I watched Pursuit of Jade for the plot)
Carries people and stuff.

676
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,680
Usually, the girl is on wires
when you carry someone.

677
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:34,000
Anyone who films costume dramas
does wire work.

678
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,200
I've never done it.

679
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,160
Me neither.

680
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,080
There are face shields too?

681
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,040
(Fully protected)

682
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,080
For the glass, right?

683
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,000
(Ke loves this look)
This face shield looks so cool.

684
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:45,980
(Gearing up)

685
00:17:46,620 --> 00:17:48,180
(Helping each other)

686
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:49,240
Like this?

687
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:50,840
Lift your bangs yourself.

688
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:52,080
Like this?

689
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,040
Show your eyebrows.

690
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,000
Like this?

691
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:55,680
Yeah.

692
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,000
This will fog up.

693
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,840
Like Iron Man.

694
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:00,320
Yeah.

695
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,080
Right? It's like Iron Man's face shield.

696
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:04,040
See if yours fogs up.

697
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:06,660
(No fog)

698
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,480
Yours isn't fogging up.

699
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:08,520
Mine isn't either.

700
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,760
Do we need to put something on it first?

701
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:12,400
With swim goggles, I think

702
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,000
you lick the whole thing.

703
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:14,840
(Tip: Saliva contains
a substance called mucin)

704
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:15,400
(Licking leaves a thin film)
Yeah.

705
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,560
(It lowers the water's surface tension)

706
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:17,750
(Stops fog droplets from forming)
You always use saliva on swim goggles.

707
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,440
Right.

708
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:20,600
So cool.

709
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:21,240
(Spots a problem)
But we won't look cool

710
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:21,640
after taking them off.

711
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:23,640
Don't take them off right away.

712
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,640
Once we take them off, everyone's

713
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:26,080
hair will be flat on top.

714
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,560
(Complimenting)
You look pretty cool.

715
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,120
(Complimenting +1)
Really cool.

716
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:30,640
Iron Man. Looks good.

717
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:33,360
Hold on. One at a time.

718
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:34,120
Okay.

719
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,400
That was pretty cool.

720
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,520
(Instantly starts acting)
One at a time.

721
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:37,500
(Shy)

722
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,000
Why are you standing here

723
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,560
showing off your irresistible charm?

724
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,620
(Teasing Ke)

725
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:44,660
(He's a big boy now.
Don't embarrass him)

726
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:47,260
(Concerned)
Pull your sleeve down.

727
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:49,360
(Film props. Do not imitate)
There'll be shards flying around.

728
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:50,240
(Thoughtful protection)
And sharp pieces too.

729
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,640
I think it's probably just plastic.

730
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,520
Plastic could still scratch you.

731
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,640
I would still worry.

732
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,760
(Asking Jin for help)
Jin, help pull this down.

733
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,920
Qian, come fix his bangs.

734
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:05,900
(Protected by the girls)

735
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:06,680
Yeah.

736
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:07,920
Good.

737
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:10,960
(Sweet talker)
You look so cool, Ning.

738
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:13,780
(Carefully fixing it)

739
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,640
Why isn't yours fogging up?

740
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,800
Did you put something on it?

741
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:17,920
No, I didn't.

742
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,180
Zhou Keyu looks like a pro in that.

743
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:21,700
(A perfect fit)

744
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,400
Why do you look so professional?

745
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,720
(New career unlocked)
I feel like I was made for this.

746
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:26,520
Doesn't he look like a speed skater?

747
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:26,920
Yeah.

748
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:28,800
You look like you do
one of those solo track events.

749
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,280
The one where you lie down in a sled.

750
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,680
Like you're really good at it.

751
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:34,700
(Hehe)

752
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,040
Put your gloves on properly.

753
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,600
Is all your other gear on?

754
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,680
Fix your clothes.

755
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,880
Let me adjust it.

756
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:43,440
Okay.

757
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,500
(Carefully fixing it)

758
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,240
(Safety first)
Don't leave any skin exposed.

759
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:47,040
All set.

760
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,040
I think your outfits

761
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:48,840
are pretty much ready.

762
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:50,160
(Your safety is my peace of mind)
Cover your hands and neck.

763
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:51,720
This is pretty hard.

764
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:53,720
(Planning their strategy)
It's fine. Here's what we'll do.

765
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:54,720
When we're at the edge,

766
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,240
(Strategy: 1. Get ready at the edge)
I'll say we're ready.

767
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:56,920
Then they'll start lowering us.

768
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:57,280
Once we move,

769
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,920
(Listening closely)
I'll say, "Guys, three, two, one, go".

770
00:19:58,920 --> 00:19:59,620
(2. Move down together)
Then we go down.

771
00:19:59,620 --> 00:20:00,440
(Focused)
We all go together.

772
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,440
(3. Push off the wall together)
Then push against the wall.

773
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,360
When I say, "Give it some slack, "

774
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,320
(4. Loosen the ropes together)
we all loosen up a little.

775
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:04,720
"Three, two, one, swing".

776
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:05,440
Then kick your way in.

777
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:09,560
(He gets it)
We push, loosen, then kick.

778
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,800
(Ding gets it)
Push, loosen, kick.

779
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,800
Then loosen it again.

780
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:13,720
Hold steady once you're there.

781
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,440
No, just loosen it once.

782
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:16,760
We need to reach this spot first.

783
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,600
(Ke gets it)
Once everyone's lined up here,

784
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,000
(Ning tries it first)
we count down and move here.

785
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,400
Start from here.

786
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:24,200
Then loosen the rope as you kick off.

787
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:25,680
You also need to stay in control.

788
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,360
You have to move from here

789
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:28,080
right as you kick off.

790
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,480
If you loosen it too much, you'll drop.

791
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:32,040
Too much is fine. Too little is worse.

792
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:33,480
(Worried)
This is so hard.

793
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:35,080
(Reassuring him)
Just let it go. You'll be fine.

794
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,040
Once we go down,

795
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,120
we can take a moment

796
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:38,880
to get a feel
for how much slack we need.

797
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,480
(Want to try it?)
Do you want to try?

798
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,120
I don't.

799
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:42,040
You really don't?

800
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:42,960
You guys do it.

801
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:45,000
You can complete your collection
of iconic moments.

802
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:45,760
It's not too bad.

803
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:47,560
Last time, we were lowered

804
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,040
from the seventh floor.

805
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,000
The seventh floor?

806
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:50,920
(Still remembers it clearly)
Was it like this?

807
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:51,960
Yeah, we went down bit by bit.

808
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,040
That's why Jin

809
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:54,640
won't even try this time.

810
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:55,960
She was terrified and cried last time.

811
00:20:58,020 --> 00:20:59,540
(In position)

812
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,080
Why does Ning look
like he's being escorted away?

813
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:06,300
(Cracking jokes to ease the tension)

814
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:08,920
Last time we did this,

815
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,160
I was terrified.

816
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,000
Ning was already losing it.

817
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:11,720
To encourage me,

818
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,960
he said, "Jin Jing, it's okay".

819
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,120
(She sees right through him)
"I'm not scared at all".

820
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:16,160
"It's fine. I'll go first".

821
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,680
I'm okay with this kind of thing.

822
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,680
But of course I'm still scared.

823
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:20,480
I once filmed a modern drama

824
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,480
where they had me do this

825
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:22,360
and jump down from about here.

826
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:23,640
Did you jump?

827
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,040
I did.

828
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:25,440
From what floor?

829
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,800
It was only this high. A few yards.

830
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,880
To succeed, first go crazy.

831
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,280
To solve the case, first go crazy.

832
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,200
You got this!

833
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:38,100
(Qian and Jin bringing the support)

834
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,280
Be careful.

835
00:21:46,460 --> 00:21:48,100
(Showtime)

836
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:51,900
(No killer yet,
but they found a "skin fragment")

837
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,080
What's this?

838
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,040
It really could be...

839
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,240
I don't know.

840
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:56,900
It kind of looks like something
from my dress.

841
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:57,540
(Nervously takes it away)

842
00:21:57,580 --> 00:21:58,260
(You're suspicious)

843
00:21:58,560 --> 00:21:59,600
Stop trying to win people over.

844
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,960
(Kicking him while he's down)
You're highly suspicious today.

845
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:02,680
Don't think you're in the clear

846
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:04,640
and can just act all relaxed.

847
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:05,720
If you keep doing this,

848
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,560
you'll only look more suspicious.

849
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:08,600
(I know what you're up to)
Don't try to get his vote.

850
00:22:08,980 --> 00:22:10,340
(Exposed without mercy)

851
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:12,000
Wait.

852
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,080
This came from Ding.

853
00:22:15,380 --> 00:22:16,620
(How am I involved now?)

854
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:18,280
(A little jab)
This is from your outfit.

855
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,080
(Calmly explaining)
I wasn't wearing this outfit then.

856
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:21,800
Then why was it at the scene?

857
00:22:22,420 --> 00:22:23,520
(This is getting juicy)
Oh, my.

858
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:25,000
I thought it came from my outfit.

859
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,600
(Explain yourself)
Ding.

860
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,200
When I killed him,

861
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:30,360
I wasn't even wearing this outfit yet.

862
00:22:30,360 --> 00:22:32,240
(Now you've made me mad)
Hey! Isn't that outside information?

863
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:33,760
(I get all fuzzy when I'm mad)
This is infuriating!

864
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,440
That comeback was so cute.

865
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:36,840
No, this is ridiculous!

866
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,360
It looks exactly like

867
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,440
the flower he had yesterday.

868
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:41,160
Why does that make it part of my outfit?

869
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,880
You're lying through your teeth.

870
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,040
(Ning doesn't buy it)
We compared it with the real thing.

871
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:45,640
Then you said...

872
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,200
It does look a lot like my outfit.

873
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,080
It doesn't just look like it.

874
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:48,600
It is.

875
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,240
It really is from his outfit.

876
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,840
(Ke steps in to be fair)
But when we filmed that part,

877
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,000
he was wearing a different jacket.

878
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Maybe when he killed him,

879
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:54,720
he didn't want blood on it,

880
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,960
so he changed clothes.

881
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:57,080
(Switching sides)
Maybe he had a backup ready.

882
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:57,600
(Perfect teamwork)
Exactly.

883
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:58,800
Okay, it's the 13 seconds in the middle.

884
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,600
Let's add a wardrobe fitting
segment too.

885
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,040
Okay.

886
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:02,860
(So you're just framing me)

887
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:07,460
(Starlight Cafe mini supply station)

888
00:23:07,460 --> 00:23:09,140
(Fishing for info on the way)
Who's got the most Golden Keys now?

889
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:10,220
Probably He.

890
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:11,460
He must have four by now.

891
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:12,740
He didn't get one yesterday.

892
00:23:12,740 --> 00:23:14,140
You've got two, right?

893
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:14,820
Two.

894
00:23:14,820 --> 00:23:16,900
I've got two, and so does He.

895
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:18,580
No way. How could he only have two?

896
00:23:18,580 --> 00:23:20,620
(You can't fool me)
He's got four Skill Cards alone.

897
00:23:20,620 --> 00:23:21,620
What are Golden Keys for?

898
00:23:21,620 --> 00:23:22,500
Bragging rights.

899
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:23,660
Just bragging rights?

900
00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:24,460
I've got zero.

901
00:23:24,460 --> 00:23:25,700
Great. That's awesome.

902
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,180
You know, when you get a Golden Key,

903
00:23:27,180 --> 00:23:28,580
(Dropping a huge hint)
you can give it to someone else.

904
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:30,420
Me? I'll never get one.

905
00:23:30,420 --> 00:23:31,510
That's totally normal.

906
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:32,900
Look, she's done three episodes
and still hasn't gotten one.

907
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:33,700
You haven't gotten a single one?

908
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:35,620
(That hurts)
Why are you rubbing it in?

909
00:23:35,620 --> 00:23:36,820
What's going on?

910
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:38,060
All of you have one?

911
00:23:38,060 --> 00:23:39,380
Not everyone does.

912
00:23:39,380 --> 00:23:41,220
(Getting cheeky)
Some people haven't gotten any.

913
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,880
Can we catch the culprit today?

914
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,240
(Confidence comes from within)
It's a lock, Ding. Trust me.

915
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:45,720
I'm kidding.

916
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,560
It's really not that simple.

917
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,160
I've already started taking notes.

918
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:49,320
I'll definitely give you guys

919
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:51,240
a solid lead.

920
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,760
If we're playing

921
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:53,440
for Golden Keys,

922
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:54,680
then we're all voting for you today.

923
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:55,600
You definitely don't have one.

924
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,760
Oh, that's how we're playing?

925
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:57,880
If it's you,

926
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:58,800
then you're wrong.

927
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,480
If it isn't you,

928
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,240
then we're all wrong.

929
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:02,760
Jin Jing's definitely the bad guy today.

930
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,800
She's acting really weird.

931
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:05,240
Ning,

932
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,880
you know what matters most to me,

933
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,880
so you just had to ruin it?

934
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:10,160
Golden Keys matter most to you?

935
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:10,600
Yeah.

936
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,480
Aren't you guys coming up?

937
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,600
Are we going
to the second or third floor?

938
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,480
The second floor.

939
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,400
Let's go.

940
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:16,960
Okay.

941
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,720
You're only walking us partway?

942
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,400
Just to the security checkpoint?

943
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:21,200
We know this place.

944
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,440
It's like going to school.

945
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,100
(Tui City Kindergarten School Run)

946
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:25,940
They're treating us like kids.

947
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:27,620
Don't put your fingers in your mouth.

948
00:24:27,620 --> 00:24:29,340
Parents never stop worrying.

949
00:24:29,340 --> 00:24:30,900
I can tell there's something here.

950
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,060
What do you mean?

951
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:33,260
Go ahead if you want a Golden Key.

952
00:24:33,260 --> 00:24:33,780
I'll do it!

953
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:34,860
Let him do it. Let him.

954
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:37,220
I was kidding. You took it seriously?

955
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,920
Nice.

956
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:43,080
We've got so many snacks today.

957
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:43,840
(Love at first bite)

958
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:45,120
Snacks!

959
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:46,720
(Living life one bite at a time)
I'm back.

960
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:49,960
Good thing I didn't eat
that protein bar.

961
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,640
(Scurrying over)
My hands are just too dirty.

962
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:53,000
They are pretty dirty.

963
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,240
(Snack thief)
I don't care.

964
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,040
Jin Cardashian.

965
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:58,600
(There's no such thing as a free lunch)
You ate my food, so you can't lie to me.

966
00:24:59,380 --> 00:25:00,420
(You can do that?)

967
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,440
Who left a banana here?

968
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,000
Jin Cardashian, it's your banana.

969
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:07,400
Have some banana.

970
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:08,840
Want some?

971
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:09,160
No.

972
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,300
(Putting it right to use)
If you eat my banana,

973
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:10,960
you can't vote for me today.

974
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,380
(Agrees instantly)
I won't.

975
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:13,400
Have one.

976
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,000
(Giving in)
My hands are just a little dirty.

977
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:16,920
This banana's really good.

978
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:19,040
It's really high in calories.

979
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:19,920
Really?

980
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:20,400
Why?

981
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,520
Dried fruit has the most calories
of all fruit.

982
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,400
(Fresh fruit has lots of water and fewer calories)
Water doesn't

983
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:24,960
(Drying fruit removes its water)
really have calories.

984
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,080
(Sugar becomes concentrated, increasing calories)
Once you remove all the water,

985
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:27,120
(Enjoy in moderation)
all that's left is calories.

986
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:27,940
(Scheming)

987
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,400
Then I'll give it to Ning.

988
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:31,820
(This can't be good)

989
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,000
Ning,

990
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:33,800
try this.

991
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:35,960
If you've touched it,

992
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,520
I have to take a bite.

993
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:38,700
(Boss Ning wisdom)

994
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:41,200
(Plan successful)
He said it's packed with calories.

995
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:42,720
It's basically sugar.

996
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,550
(High-calorie food tastes better)
It's all sugar.

997
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,600
Bananas are also high in calories.

998
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:46,680
Really?

999
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:48,400
Yeah, bananas are high in calories.

1000
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,520
This is high in calories too.

1001
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:51,480
This one's not too bad.

1002
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,520
Beef isn't that bad.

1003
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,040
No, there's a lot of sugar in it.

1004
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:55,040
Can't you taste the sugar?

1005
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,120
It's still better than yours.

1006
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,380
(Taste comes first)

1007
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,400
Is there a trash can?

1008
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:00,840
Give it to me.

1009
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:02,760
I'll toss it for you.

1010
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,280
This couch is so comfy.

1011
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,120
What's this? Durian?

1012
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,160
(Still milking the pun)
It's Liu Lian Wangfan's durian.

1013
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,360
(A very happy eater)
It's really good.

1014
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:18,840
It's really good.

1015
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:19,960
I'm really scared of durian.

1016
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:20,900
(He's scared, but Ke can eat it)

1017
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,260
(He loves sharing)

1018
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:24,460
(The Let's Go Food Detectives)

1019
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:27,520
What's this?

1020
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,600
Sugar-free beef jerky.

1021
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:29,760
His has sugar.

1022
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:30,720
(The siblings quietly share snacks)
This one's sweetened.

1023
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,480
The darker one's sugar-free.

1024
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:34,200
(That's the good stuff)
The sweetened one's better.

1025
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:37,740
(Life's all about eating)

1026
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:39,120
(Banana, no payback)
I ate your banana.

1027
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:39,720
I won't vote for you.

1028
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:42,040
I'll seriously be mad
if you vote for me today.

1029
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:42,660
(A serious warning)

1030
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:43,380
(Laughing before she even says it)

1031
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,000
Or you won't get the Golden Key.

1032
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:47,360
It's fine.

1033
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,360
(Ke knows the drill)
They all say that before voting.

1034
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:51,560
Aren't you guys eating
the bread Pudding made?

1035
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:52,960
Whose bread?

1036
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:53,520
My bread?

1037
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:54,760
It's yours.

1038
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:55,400
You won it.

1039
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:57,040
Break off half for me.

1040
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,000
(Easygoing Ding)
Sure.

1041
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:58,960
We'll split it.

1042
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:00,680
(Extending an invitation)
Let's share this.

1043
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,720
(Helping everyone at once)
Let's share it.

1044
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:02,840
Ding, you break it.

1045
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:03,940
(You've got a new order)

1046
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:04,720
You break it.

1047
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:07,520
Didn't we just finish eating?

1048
00:27:07,540 --> 00:27:09,100
(There's always room for dessert)

1049
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,640
(Eating the cafe out of business)
Look at this.

1050
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:11,800
I want that one.

1051
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:13,760
Who'll split one with me?

1052
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:15,200
No one.

1053
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,840
♪Half and half♪

1054
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,600
(Breaking into song anywhere)
♪But I don't want it♪

1055
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:22,400
♪Half and half♪

1056
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,600
♪But the two of us...♪

1057
00:27:23,660 --> 00:27:24,260
(That hit the funny bone)

1058
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:27,160
(Still savoring it)
♪Half and half♪

1059
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:28,880
Art films love using

1060
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,680
Sichuan-Chongqing dialects now.

1061
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:32,080
Right.

1062
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,520
(Full approval from Sichuan and Chongqing)
That dialect's so hot right now.

1063
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:34,880
It's not always that dialect.

1064
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:36,640
It depends where the story's set.

1065
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:38,920
But it sounds so powerful.

1066
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:41,440
It feels authentic and textured.

1067
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,160
Right.

1068
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,240
Where are you from? Shenyang?

1069
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,040
The Northeast.

1070
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:44,560
Harbin.

1071
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:45,520
I'm from Harbin too.

1072
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:46,140
(Making it up on the spot)

1073
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:47,560
You're from Harbin too?

1074
00:27:47,560 --> 00:27:48,420
(Fellow Harbin native)
Really?

1075
00:27:49,140 --> 00:27:50,220
(Are you?)

1076
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:51,780
(Memory malfunction)

1077
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:53,220
(You little...)

1078
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:56,760
(Busted instantly)
Don't let him fool you.

1079
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,020
Why do you still love
messing with people?

1080
00:27:59,020 --> 00:27:59,660
(Why didn't you include me?)

1081
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,600
When did you become like this?

1082
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,000
Bad Ding.

1083
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,840
Only the killer's allowed to lie.

1084
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:06,140
(Adding fuel to the fire)

1085
00:28:06,180 --> 00:28:06,980
(There's no clearing his name now)

1086
00:28:07,620 --> 00:28:08,300
(Cracking instantly)

1087
00:28:08,780 --> 00:28:09,420
(This is hilarious)

1088
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:11,880
You can do that?

1089
00:28:12,120 --> 00:28:12,880
(Out of options)
Fine.

1090
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:13,960
We

1091
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:15,520
still have two stories

1092
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:16,440
(Still focused on the case)
to finish.

1093
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:16,960
Mine.

1094
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:18,480
And Jin's.

1095
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,560
What story?

1096
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:21,880
